-Your wife got one of those
Amway franchises?

04:29.811 --> 04:33.690
Well, it-it's not Amway,
but it's a similar principle.

04:33.690 --> 04:37.527
I could, uh, definitely use
a vitamin supplement, and
that's a reasonable price.

04:37.527 --> 04:39.904
Yeah. Yeah. She said
the products are
excellent and...

04:39.904 --> 04:43.533
-the prices are very reasonable.
-Nice hairbrush.

04:43.533 --> 04:46.744
Now, there is absolutely
no obligation to buy anything,

04:46.744 --> 04:48.413
and if anything is not
to your satisfaction,

04:48.413 --> 04:51.165
-you get a full refund.
-I use this shampoo.

04:51.165 --> 04:56.087
Absolutely no obligation.

04:56.087 --> 04:59.132
-Can I help you?
-Our name is Hastings.

04:59.132 --> 05:01.551
We need to talk to someone
about a robbery.

05:01.551 --> 05:05.638
Greg. James? Detectives Medavoy
and Martinez will help you.

05:05.638 --> 05:08.725
Those are samples,
I'm gonna put those away.

05:08.725 --> 05:11.311
-Is that Jill Kirkendall?
-Can I help you, folks?

05:11.311 --> 05:14.230
Would you be more
comfortable talking with
Detective Kirkendall?

05:14.230 --> 05:15.898
-Would that be possible?
-Um, Jill?

05:15.898 --> 05:18.693
-Diane? They know Jill, so--
-Hey!

05:18.693 --> 05:20.820
-She and Diane can
work the complaint.
-MEDAVOY: Sure.

05:20.820 --> 05:24.907
-Ah, 12.95 for the vitamins?
-Don't do that here, Greg.

05:24.907 --> 05:27.785
-It's been so long
since we've seen you.
-How's Lucinda?

05:27.785 --> 05:30.455
Oh, Marshall,
you remember Jill.

05:30.455 --> 05:34.500
-You're a detective now.
-Yeah. Excuse me.

05:34.500 --> 05:37.462
Diane, could I work
this interview alone?

05:38.504 --> 05:40.548
