it was mostly little things.
Going into my purse.

06:41.943 --> 06:44.195
More embarrassing
than anything.

06:44.195 --> 06:46.989
So, Lucinda was living with you
after the divorce?

06:46.989 --> 06:49.575
-Oh, she still comes
over, of course--
-She comes over...

06:49.575 --> 06:52.870
after we threw her out,
and last night...

06:52.870 --> 06:56.791
she stole from us again--
and this is the end of it.

06:56.791 --> 06:59.585
-What did she steal?
-A Mont Blanc pen...

06:59.585 --> 07:03.256
which was a law school
graduation present
from my father.

07:03.256 --> 07:08.052
In terms of the criminal
aspects, their value to us
is largely sentimental.

07:08.052 --> 07:11.055
-Lucy still using drugs?
-Oh, she's been in programs--

07:11.055 --> 07:14.267
She's using drugs, yes.

07:14.267 --> 07:18.062
My daughter is a thief
and a drug addict.

07:18.062 --> 07:21.816
-That sums it up.
-And you're here
to press charges.

07:21.816 --> 07:23.192
That's why we're here.

07:26.195 --> 07:31.033
If the items could be
retrieved, is that something
that would satisfy you?

07:31.033 --> 07:33.035
And maybe if Lucy
went back in a program?

07:33.035 --> 07:35.788
Not another
damned country club!

07:39.625 --> 07:43.254
If you'd list the items,
and, uh, where I can find Lucy.

07:47.633 --> 07:50.553
(pen scratching paper)

07:50.928 --> 07:53.931
