10:28.002 --> 10:30.379
-How much?
-Lucy?

10:32.089 --> 10:37.261
-(baby crying)
-Oh, my God! Jill Kirkendall!

10:37.261 --> 10:41.390
What are you doing here?
I-I'm such a jerk, I-I thought
you were Chinese food.

10:41.390 --> 10:44.894
-Can I come in?
-Yeah, sure.

10:44.894 --> 10:48.105
Uh, I'm such a slob.
(laughs)

10:49.231 --> 10:52.234
My God, you look--
You look fantastic!

10:52.234 --> 10:56.989
-Thanks. How're you doing, Lucy?
-Geez, I haven't seen you
since high school.

10:56.989 --> 10:59.200
-You know, I-I think
it was.
-(gasps)

11:00.618 --> 11:03.621
So, what's happened
in the last 20 years?

11:03.621 --> 11:07.708
Oh, uh, marriage,
uh, two kids--divorce--

11:07.708 --> 11:10.252
Men. That entire gender
is defective.

11:10.252 --> 11:13.673
Well, I'm raising two,
so I try to keep an open mind.

11:13.673 --> 11:16.967
Anyway,
I became a detective.
(lighter clicks)

11:16.967 --> 11:18.886
Uh-oh.
(chuckles)

11:18.886 --> 11:22.306
Well, I hope this is
just a social call.

11:22.306 --> 11:25.893
I'm really glad to see you
again, but your parents
filed a complaint...

11:25.893 --> 11:27.937
about some things that were
taken from their apartment.

11:27.937 --> 11:29.647
Well, that's
a new line of attack.

11:29.647 --> 11:32.400
Usually they send
shrinks, ex-nuns--

11:34.443 --> 11:37.863
Did you take
those things, Lucy?

11:37.863 --> 11:40.825
You know, I'd ask
for a lawyer, but my parents
would have to hire him.

11:46.664 --> 11:48.624
You using?

11:50.376 --> 11:53.838
It must be the super's.
(laughing)

11:53.838 --> 11:56.048
Look, um, truth is,

11:56.048 --> 11:58.134
this guy I hang with,
he's cute but trouble.

11:58.134 --> 12:01.137
What can I say? You know
those models that look
like junkies? Guess what.

12:01.137 --> 12:02.888
They are!

12:06.642 --> 12:09.562
Hey, who's this?

12:09.562 --> 12:11.897
-That's my Jenny.
-Oh.

12:11.897 --> 12:16.694
I was married 10 months to
a major asshole. Left me about
two weeks before she was born.

12:16.694 --> 12:22.116
