decided that I was unfit, and
gave her to my cousin Frank.

12:22.116 --> 12:25.327
-Did you fight it?
-Please, you try
fighting my father.

12:25.327 --> 12:27.913
I get to see her some.

12:27.913 --> 12:31.709
When I can hold on
to train fare for
more than a day.

12:31.709 --> 12:34.211
So, this stuff you stole,
you still have it?

12:35.129 --> 12:38.090
What, my dad give you
an earful about
the Mont Blanc?

12:38.090 --> 12:39.967
You know, he's got
Parkinson's disease.

12:39.967 --> 12:43.137
He feels like
the world let him down.
It all lands on me.

12:43.137 --> 12:45.389
You know, if you
only knew how many times--

12:45.389 --> 12:48.184
how many times I had
to listen to how my gramps...

12:48.184 --> 12:51.562
just made it out of
the vineyard for Dad's
graduating Yale Law,

12:51.562 --> 12:54.732
-giving him that stupid pen.
-They want that stuff back,

12:54.732 --> 12:58.068
-or you could
get locked up, Lucy.
-(sighs) God.

12:59.737 --> 13:02.406
-I sold that stuff last night.
-On the street?

13:02.406 --> 13:04.950
