17:00.227 --> 17:02.980
(sniffs)
I mean, I just really
gotta go meet some people.

17:02.980 --> 17:05.607
-Meaning you've gotta
get high.
-Oh, I gotta go,

17:05.607 --> 17:07.818
so that means
I'm gonna score drugs, right?

17:07.818 --> 17:10.404
You need to get into a program,
Lucy. That's the condition...

17:10.404 --> 17:14.700
-of your parents
not pursuing charges.
-Sure. Okay. Fine!

17:14.700 --> 17:17.202
You've got an intake
interview in half an hour
at Phoenix House.

17:17.202 --> 17:19.997
-I want to
take you over there.
-Just look! Look!

17:19.997 --> 17:22.416
Sit down!

17:22.416 --> 17:25.335
Jill, it's ju--
You made your point.

17:37.222 --> 17:39.433
Here's my address
and phone number.

17:42.269 --> 17:43.687
I'm not passing you off.

17:43.687 --> 17:46.023
-(scoffing)
-But you've got
to understand.

17:46.023 --> 17:50.027
Either I take you to that
program, or you're a collar.

17:50.027 --> 17:53.781
Boy, I'm really, really glad
we got back in touch, Jill.

18:01.246 --> 18:05.459
Diane, pross D.O.A.,
4th and "D."

18:05.459 --> 18:08.420
-Any description on the pross?
-No. Work it with her?

18:14.134 --> 18:15.886
Thanks.
Yeah.

18:19.556 --> 18:22.559
♪♪

18:34.279 --> 18:37.491
He/She pross,
hacked up pretty good.

18:37.491 --> 18:40.494
Oh, son of a bitch.
(gasps)

18:40.494 --> 18:42.913
There was another hooker
here screaming,
but she ran away.

18:42.913 --> 18:45.290
-Black girl?
-Got a license plate number.

18:45.290 --> 18:47.501
-Someone tacked it to a pole.
-Yeah, we'll run that.

18:47.501 --> 18:50.254
-What the hell's the point?
-It's gonna be the boyfriend.

18:50.254 --> 18:52.589
Let's go pick
the stupid bastard up.

18:54.967 --> 18:57.094
Hey, you all right?

19:20.868 --> 19:23.871
♪♪

19:30.794 --> 19:32.337
Detective Medavoy's
called in sick?

19:32.337 --> 19:34.590
Said he had
a bad upset stomach.

19:34.590 --> 19:37.426
Let me call him up.

19:37.426 --> 19:40.304
Come in like storm troopers
to a man's place of work?

19:40.304 --> 19:42.598
Up all night, plus
we're storm troopers?

19:42.598 --> 19:45.017
Looked to me like you
came in pretty voluntarily
there, Mr. Drury.

19:45.017 --> 19:48.020
-To avoid humiliation.
-Next time when you
get a polite request...

19:48.020 --> 19:50.981
on the phone,
you'll think twice
about not hanging up.

19:50.981 --> 19:54.067
FANCY:
His line's busy. Did he say
what the upset was from?

19:54.067 --> 19:57.571
GINA:
Just got the impression
it was like a stomach virus.

19:57.571 --> 19:59.406
-Oh, morning.
-Yeah, we got this guy in.

19:59.406 --> 20:02.951
Someone put his
license plate number up where
the prostitute got murdered.

20:02.951 --> 20:06.580
-So, you're looking at him
as a witness or the perp?
-Well, maybe a trick.

20:06.580 --> 20:09.166
He could've seen something.
We still gotta like
the boyfriend for doing her.

20:09.166 --> 20:12.461
-Yeah, and he's in the wind.
-We sat on his place
all night.

20:12.461 --> 20:16.173
We're also looking for
the black pross who used to
hang around with the D.O.A.

20:16.173 --> 20:18.842
-Morning, Lieu.
-Yeah. Um, did you happen
to speak with Greg?

20:18.842 --> 20:20.844
Yeah, he's got some
kind of stomach difficulty.

20:20.844 --> 20:23.847
Lieu, I'm gonna
talk to this guy.

20:23.847 --> 20:25.432
Did he say it was
vitamin-related?

20:25.432 --> 20:27.059
-His stomach problem?
-Mm-hmm.

20:27.059 --> 20:29.728
-He didn't say,
one way or another.
-Yeah, okay.

20:31.939 --> 20:33.607
-Hey, Gina.
-Hey, James.

20:38.403 --> 20:39.321
Hmm.

20:39.321 --> 20:42.407
Not one damn bit
of concern for damage
to a person's reputation?

20:42.407 --> 20:45.410
-We're still on this
interesting subject.
-SIMONE: What is that?

20:45.410 --> 20:47.329
Is that an uneasy conscience
there, Mr. Drury,

20:47.329 --> 20:50.040
reading so much into
your coworker's reactions?

20:50.040 --> 20:54.044
How 'bout if your wife
knew we were talking to you?
That've wound you up even more?

20:54.044 --> 20:57.256
So, did you transact any,
uh, personal business...

20:57.256 --> 20:59.258
before going home
from work yesterday?

20:59.258 --> 21:01.468
An alley off of 4th and "D."

21:01.468 --> 21:04.888
-You people are scum.
-No one is looking to
embarrass you here, all right?

21:04.888 --> 21:08.100
We are investigating
a murder, and we're trying
to get you to cooperate.

21:08.100 --> 21:10.727
I have nothing to do
with that. A murder.

21:10.727 --> 21:14.189
We figure that's
absolutely possible,
so why don't you stop...

21:14.189 --> 21:17.359
your pissing
and moaning how everyone's
infringing your good name,

21:17.359 --> 21:21.530
tell us what you know,
so my partner and me can
do a little freshening up.

21:21.530 --> 21:23.865
This can be kept from
my employer and my family?

21:23.865 --> 21:26.285
We need to know what
you saw, Mr. Drury.

21:26.285 --> 21:31.206
(sighs)
Okay. We got into the car--

21:31.206 --> 21:34.251
-Wait. Wait. Back up.
-What?

21:34.251 --> 21:36.670
You picked her up
on the street?

21:36.670 --> 21:38.672
Just in that immediate
vicinity.

21:38.672 --> 21:43.510
And she asked if I wanted to
go to a hotel, and I didn't have
time, so we went into the alley.

21:43.510 --> 21:46.638
-She was just starting
to undo my trousers--
-You'd paid her?

21:46.638 --> 21:51.727
Forty dollars. And before
anything else could happen,

21:51.727 --> 21:55.355
her pimp or some street thief
came up to the window
on my side...

21:55.355 --> 21:58.275
and opened the door,
and held a knife to my throat.

21:58.275 --> 22:00.110
You had your door unlocked?

22:00.110 --> 22:04.281
I wanted to be able to get
away quickly in-in-in case
she decided to rob me.

22:04.281 --> 22:07.284
Anyway, uh, he took
my money and threw my wallet
on the floor,

22:07.284 --> 22:08.869
and then headed around
the front of the car.

22:08.869 --> 22:13.498
-I-I was just glad
enough to get away.
-And she was still in the car?

22:13.498 --> 22:16.710
She, um--She got out.
She was screaming at him.

22:16.710 --> 22:20.339
I don't know if they were
working together, or if the
screaming was a show or what.

22:20.339 --> 22:22.424
You see anybody else around?

22:22.424 --> 22:26.553
A black hooker came running.
I almost ran her over.

22:26.553 --> 22:30.515
-Describe the guy
who robbed you.
-(inhales) Uh, muscular.

22:30.515 --> 22:33.685
Um, medium height.
Hispanic.

22:35.020 --> 22:36.813
All right,
thanks, Mr. Drury.

22:36.813 --> 22:39.483
We may want you
to come back in later
on for a lineup.

22:39.483 --> 22:41.526
I will not testify
in any open forum.

22:41.526 --> 22:46.156
He said he might need you
for a lineup. Stop yellin'
before you're hit.

22:46.156 --> 22:48.075
-Can I go?
-Okay.

22:51.745 --> 22:54.164
(sighs deeply)
(door slams)

22:55.957 --> 22:58.543
Wash up, hit Peaches's stroll?

22:58.543 --> 23:02.005
Yeah. Think
if he'd have known about
Angela's johnson down there,

23:02.005 --> 23:04.049
that would have been
an unhappy surprise?

23:04.049 --> 23:05.926
That would've been
the anchovy on the pizza.

23:11.390 --> 23:14.101
-Hi.
-Oh, hi.

23:14.101 --> 23:17.312
Um, could you close the door?

23:17.312 --> 23:21.358
The way you sounded on
the phone, I thought I might
find you in restraints.

23:21.358 --> 23:22.818
This won't work, Lillian.

23:22.818 --> 23:25.946
You need to take these
product samples home.

23:25.946 --> 23:29.491
Obviously, I've come to
take 'em. But I'd like us
to take one whirl...

23:29.491 --> 23:32.744
-at discussing
this rationally.
-Medavoy's sick.

23:32.744 --> 23:36.790
-God knows what that's about.
-I don't think it's about
the vitamins you sold him.

23:36.790 --> 23:39.126
And I don't want to have to
wonder about that, Lillian.

23:39.126 --> 23:43.213
Or worry that
Gina's buying mints to
curry favor with her boss.

23:43.213 --> 23:45.924
I can see where
that might be a problem.

23:45.924 --> 23:49.845
But it seems to me, uh,
an articulate and fair-minded
person like yourself...

23:49.845 --> 23:52.222
can communicate
that's the opposite
of what would happen.

23:52.222 --> 23:56.351
-I told them
not to feel obligated.
-I'm sure they believed you.

23:56.351 --> 23:58.395
It's you that can't accept
that's the case.

23:58.395 --> 24:03.066
(sighs)
This company's been
in business for 23 years.

24:03.066 --> 24:07.237
And 60 Minutes does
exposés all the time about
these pyramid schemes.

24:07.237 --> 24:11.783
You're worried about
distributors selling franchises.
I'm not doing that.

24:11.783 --> 24:15.871
This is crazy. We had this
conversation last night.

24:15.871 --> 24:19.499
Look, with the girls in school,
I know we need the extra income,

24:19.499 --> 24:22.043
but I don't want
anyone thinkin'--

24:22.043 --> 24:25.213
-Don't shake your head at me.
-I'll take these home.

24:25.213 --> 24:27.632
What are you shaking
your head for?

24:29.885 --> 24:33.221
I'd like to take that boob that
sits in judgment in your head,

24:33.221 --> 24:34.639
and punch him in the nose.

24:36.433 --> 24:39.686
I'm sorry.
(rustling paper)

24:39.686 --> 24:42.105
Will you at least tell
people they can call me?

24:42.105 --> 24:44.649
-With no obligation.
-No, Arthur.

24:44.649 --> 24:48.445
If they call and don't buy,
I'm gonna come
and beat 'em with a stick.

24:50.405 --> 24:54.075
-I love you.
-I love you back.

24:56.453 --> 24:59.372
Mr. Hastings?
Mrs. Hastings?

25:01.541 --> 25:04.377
Can you identify
these items for me?

25:08.006 --> 25:13.011
That's my pen.
That's your grandmother's
necklace and earrings.

25:13.011 --> 25:16.097
-And is that everything
that was taken?
-Yes.

25:16.097 --> 25:18.725
-I suppose so.
-Good.

25:18.725 --> 25:21.228
-Will you sign this for me?
-Sure.

25:21.228 --> 25:24.731
You'll need to go to
that address I've indicated
to take it out of pawn.

25:24.731 --> 25:28.485
Lucinda enrolled
at Phoenix House yesterday.

25:28.485 --> 25:30.612
I promise you,
it's not a country club.

25:31.696 --> 25:34.658
I can't tell you
how grateful we are.

25:35.825 --> 25:39.037
Mrs. Hastings,
you need to understand...

25:39.037 --> 25:42.040
that Lucinda's
trying to get well
is a long, hard process...

25:42.040 --> 25:44.334
and doesn't have
the world's greatest
success rate.

25:44.334 --> 25:47.796
She's never understood that.
She doesn't want to now.

25:47.796 --> 25:50.215
Mr. Hastings,
I'm sure you understand.

25:50.215 --> 25:56.137
Knowing the process is hard, and
Lucy might not succeed, doesn't
mean you stop loving her.

25:56.137 --> 26:00.475
It means your life
can't revolve around
whether she does or doesn't.

26:00.475 --> 26:02.435
Other people
are suffering too.

26:06.690 --> 26:11.820
I told Lucy to use this
whenever she felt the need.

26:11.820 --> 26:14.531
I hope you'll do the same.

26:14.531 --> 26:16.783
Can we call Lucy?

26:16.783 --> 26:19.119
I think you should wait
till she calls you first.

26:19.119 --> 26:23.832
Jill, I feel this is just
a turning of the corner.

26:23.832 --> 26:28.378
-I'm just so optimistic.
-Thanks for your help.

26:28.378 --> 26:33.425
Sure. Ah, can you
show yourselves out?

26:41.266 --> 26:45.437
We got our thumbs up our butts
pretty good. Perp liable
presently...

26:45.437 --> 26:47.272
to be relocated
to San Juan.

26:47.272 --> 26:49.566
Now this Peaches
is in the wind.

26:49.566 --> 26:52.319
Yeah, Peaches in the wind
probably means Jimmy Cortez
is still around.

26:52.319 --> 26:54.904
You figure
she's hiding from him?

26:54.904 --> 26:56.990
What makes you think so clear
after being up all night?

26:56.990 --> 27:00.577
We've gotta find Peaches,
and we gotta sit on this guy
Cortez's place again.

27:00.577 --> 27:03.204
How would you put out
a description on her?

27:03.204 --> 27:06.750
"Subject looks like Rolonda
or Godfrey Cambridge."

27:06.750 --> 27:09.544
(stifles laugh)
That's accurate, Bobby.

27:10.670 --> 27:13.465
Crime's down.
Crime's down.

27:13.465 --> 27:16.676
They always come up with
these full-of-nonsense
statistics.

27:16.676 --> 27:20.096
Look at that cheek of yours.
I'd just as soon
not talk about it.

27:20.096 --> 27:22.390
You know, you need to get you
a little piece for your purse.

27:22.390 --> 27:25.685
-Arthur Cartwell.
-Says he has information
on your case.

27:25.685 --> 27:29.814
Yeah. He's got information
on every case, including that
big blimp that caught on fire.

27:29.814 --> 27:34.027
-Which one crashed? Not Snoopy?
-What do you got, Arthur?

27:34.027 --> 27:38.406
I'd like to communicate
in somewhat more confidential
surroundings.

27:38.406 --> 27:40.575
Oh, absolutely.

27:50.585 --> 27:54.422
-You look like something
the cat dragged in.
-Sleepless night.

27:59.052 --> 28:01.262
-So!
-So?

28:01.262 --> 28:05.100
So.
(coughs)

28:05.100 --> 28:10.063
Pretty pross named Angela,
she no longer amongst us.

28:10.063 --> 28:12.190
-Give it up, Cartwell.
-How 'bout you giving up...

28:12.190 --> 28:14.859
how much a eyewitness I.D.
gonna be worth?

28:16.236 --> 28:18.863
Being as how, uh, that
Willie Lopez clearance...

28:18.863 --> 28:23.493
put big feathers in y'all's
caps, and left me 'bout
as poor as when I woke up.

28:23.493 --> 28:26.788
I.D. and an eyewitness
testimony will get you
a couple thousand.

28:26.788 --> 28:29.582
But you gotta make all
the hearings, Arthur.

28:29.582 --> 28:31.710
I'm familiar with
how them wheels turn.

28:31.710 --> 28:34.879
Are we hearing chapter and verse
any point in the near future?

28:37.132 --> 28:40.760
Jimmy Cortez did Angela.
Cut her up in that alley
like a bird.

28:40.760 --> 28:44.139
-Which you saw from where?
-Across the street in a car.

28:44.139 --> 28:46.933
They're in the street having
a shouting match, then he take
her over in that alley...

28:46.933 --> 28:49.769
start cuttin' on her--

28:49.769 --> 28:53.690
I mean, I'm like, "Oh, man,"
but, you know, before I could
do anything, he gone.

28:53.690 --> 28:55.817
Hmm. What were
they fighting about?

28:55.817 --> 29:01.197
I don't know. I guess
it was a-a lover's quarrel.

29:01.197 --> 29:04.534
You know, certain elements.
You know, they--everybody
know they got a thing.

29:04.534 --> 29:10.915
-Anybody else around there?
-Uh-uh. But y'all got me.

29:10.915 --> 29:13.001
Hmm. You're lying, Arthur.

29:13.001 --> 29:15.670
See, now there you go
with this doubtin' me.

29:15.670 --> 29:19.966
That black whore send you
in here, huh? Told you what
she saw, clean up the story?

29:19.966 --> 29:22.051
I don't have the faintest idea
what you're talking about.

29:22.051 --> 29:25.013
Oh, sure you do, Arthur.
You see, we know
Peaches was there.

29:25.013 --> 29:28.600
She's afraid to testify.
She wants this guy collared,
she comes to you.

29:28.600 --> 29:33.730
(coughs) Okay.
Say that this is so.

29:33.730 --> 29:37.150
Cortez did do Angela.
Y'all want the clearance.

29:37.150 --> 29:39.736
-Shut up!
-Where we gonna find
Peaches, Arthur?

29:39.736 --> 29:43.782
-How much that gonna be worth?
-You not needin' to have
your jaw reset.

29:48.369 --> 29:49.496
C-note.

29:51.748 --> 29:52.999
(clicks tongue)

29:57.504 --> 30:02.425
-This is where you'll find her.
-You know what'd be
worth more?

30:02.425 --> 30:08.848
Now, I will now turn my
attentions on where that evil
Puerto Rican's hiding out.

30:08.848 --> 30:12.977
You see, I just oughta be
made an honorary member
of this department.

30:15.396 --> 30:17.190
Detective, I didn't know
where you were.

30:17.190 --> 30:19.776
-What is it, Gina?
-You have a male
babysitter at home?

30:19.776 --> 30:21.611
-What's wrong?
-He wants you to come home.

30:21.611 --> 30:24.614
Says he let someone in you gave
your card to, now he's worried
what they're doing.

30:24.614 --> 30:27.992
-Tell the Lieutenant
I'm taking lost time.
-All right.

30:27.992 --> 30:30.203
-I need to get through.
-You okay, Jill?

30:30.203 --> 30:32.622
-I need to get home.
-Busy, busy, busy.

30:32.622 --> 30:34.833
Shut up, Cartwell.

30:37.460 --> 30:40.463
♪♪

30:43.258 --> 30:45.260
(knocking)

30:48.054 --> 30:50.390
-Are the boys all right?
-I couldn't reach you,
and she said that...

30:50.390 --> 30:52.684
-you told her to come here.
-This is Lucinda Hastings.

30:52.684 --> 30:54.477
-She showed me your card.
-Hi, Mom!

30:54.477 --> 30:58.439
-Hi, Sweetheart! Hi.
-She looks bad. I didn't know
if I should call the hospital.

30:58.439 --> 31:00.733
-We got a sleepover.
-We do, huh?

31:00.733 --> 31:03.820
-Lying down in your room.
-Her name's Lucy.
She looks pretty sick.

31:03.820 --> 31:06.406
Oh. Well, I'll tell you what.

31:06.406 --> 31:09.993
You guys stay here,
and I'm gonna go see
how Lucy's feeling, okay?

31:09.993 --> 31:10.952
-Okay.
-All right.

31:10.952 --> 31:12.787
Stay with the boys.

31:17.917 --> 31:19.335
-(moaning)
-Oh, sh--

31:22.672 --> 31:24.799
-(sighs deeply)
-Jill.

31:24.799 --> 31:28.303
-What did you take, Lucy?
-Nothing. I'm too sick.

31:28.303 --> 31:31.890
I'm not asking you
what you stole. I'm asking
what drugs you took.

31:31.890 --> 31:34.893
I was trying for smack,
but it was a beat bag.

31:34.893 --> 31:36.936
-You don't know what was in it?
-No. (gasping)

31:36.936 --> 31:40.273
-Emmett!
-Walked out of that program,

31:40.273 --> 31:43.484
and tried to trick a cop
but it was a beat bag.

31:43.484 --> 31:45.778
Call an ambulance
and shut the door.

31:47.488 --> 31:50.116
So, when the bag was bad
you came back here to rob me?

31:51.242 --> 31:54.621
Still had to get off.

31:54.621 --> 31:57.999
I wasn't attracting too many
johns throwing up on myself.
(laughing)

31:58.708 --> 32:01.920
-Can I get some water?
-No, I don't want to put
anything in your stomach...

32:01.920 --> 32:04.923
-until we know what's going on.
-God, you've got so many rules.

32:04.923 --> 32:07.216
-(knocking)
-BOY: Mom, can I come in?

32:07.216 --> 32:10.762
-No, sweetheart.
-I want to draw
a picture for ya.

32:10.762 --> 32:14.641
-We'll do it later.
-(grunts)

32:14.641 --> 32:19.896
-What's gonna happen now?
-We'll get you taken care
of at the hospital.

32:19.896 --> 32:23.358
-Then you're going to jail.
-(sobbing)

32:32.700 --> 32:35.411
I ain't gonna be a part of it.

32:35.411 --> 32:38.414
Peaches, you reached out
to someone else to give
a perjured statement...

32:38.414 --> 32:40.500
'cause you wanted
this guy collared.

32:40.500 --> 32:42.877
(sobs)
Did you see how he cut her?

32:42.877 --> 32:46.923
-We'll protect you from Cortez.
-How you protected Angela?

32:46.923 --> 32:48.925
She came here and
begged you for help.

32:48.925 --> 32:50.551
There was nothing
we could do there, Peaches.

32:50.551 --> 32:52.720
Bring the D.A.
a whore getting slapped,

32:52.720 --> 32:55.181
all's we're gonna
get is, "Don't let
the door hit your ass."

32:55.181 --> 32:57.433
Murder's a different
story, Peaches.

32:57.433 --> 33:00.228
Eyewitness, you'll get housing,
D.A.'s squad looking after you.

33:00.228 --> 33:03.940
(sobs)
She was my friend, you know?

33:03.940 --> 33:07.402
-We were friends for six years.
-I know that.

33:08.361 --> 33:11.531
Here we go with the faucets.

33:11.531 --> 33:17.495
I'll make you this promise,
and I'll promise
Angela at her grave.

33:17.495 --> 33:21.958
Some future day when
Jimmy's unaware,

33:21.958 --> 33:24.419
I will come and take
a razor to him.

33:24.419 --> 33:28.464
But don't do nothing
simple, like give up
a statement now.

33:28.464 --> 33:33.511
When he's unaware, 'cause
a cut throat don't entail
walking around on bail.

33:33.511 --> 33:35.555
(knocking on door)

33:37.015 --> 33:40.226
-What's going on?
-That, uh, snitch Cartwell
says he can...

33:40.226 --> 33:42.061
put you with your perp.

33:47.191 --> 33:51.195
Peaches, we gotta go somewhere.
I-I'm gonna get Hank to take
you home, all right?

33:51.195 --> 33:53.656
-Sure. Whatever.
-I'll get Hank.

34:03.332 --> 34:04.625
CORTEZ:
I'm gonna get you, Cartwell.

34:04.625 --> 34:06.586
CARTWELL:
-Hey, batter, batter--
-Let me outta here!

34:06.586 --> 34:09.505
-Batter, batter, batter--
-CORTEZ:
Let me outta here, Cartwell!

34:09.505 --> 34:12.508
'Cause you're not going
nowhere, my brother!
(tires screech)

34:12.508 --> 34:15.261
-Let me outta here!
-CARTWELL:
Do just like I said.

34:15.261 --> 34:16.679
I'll be damned
if he don't got him.

34:16.679 --> 34:18.514
SIMONE: What's he got,
a board blocking the door?

34:18.514 --> 34:21.184
Here's your man,
Jimmy Cortez, trapped like
the Mighty Joe Young.

34:21.184 --> 34:23.311
You're the greatest, Arthur.
Now, get outta here.

34:23.311 --> 34:26.564
-RUSSELL: Get back.
-Shoo! Hard evidence!

34:26.564 --> 34:28.733
-You, me and Jimmy Cortez.
-Get outta here now.

34:28.733 --> 34:30.610
It's not too late
in the day to get that
money issued, is it?

34:30.610 --> 34:33.571
-Just call us in the morning.
-I'm going
down there, my brother.

34:33.571 --> 34:35.239
-Ready!
-Calm down here.
Drop that phone.

34:35.239 --> 34:38.242
This case has been
humiliating in every aspect.

34:38.242 --> 34:41.662
Get that phone thing.
Come on, take it out.

34:41.662 --> 34:43.873
Just calm down.

34:43.873 --> 34:47.376
-You scummy little snake!
-SIPOWICZ: Yeah, can't argue
with you there, Jimmy.

34:47.376 --> 34:49.504
-You better hope
I don't get out!
-Shut the hell up!

34:49.504 --> 34:51.547
Put 'em over your head!

34:55.843 --> 34:58.429
All right. It's all over.
It's all over.

35:07.480 --> 35:09.065
Detective.

35:10.650 --> 35:12.777
(whispers)
I gotta go.

35:18.032 --> 35:21.202
(sighs)
Hi. I hope
I'm not bothering you.

35:21.202 --> 35:23.204
-No.
-You gave me your card.

35:23.204 --> 35:24.956
How can I help you,
Mrs. Hastings?

35:24.956 --> 35:26.999
I've just come from
the hospital.

35:26.999 --> 35:29.127
The doctors seemed
to feel Lucy was stable.

35:29.127 --> 35:33.172
She is so sick. I was
so grateful to you, Jill,

35:33.172 --> 35:35.758
for helping us retrieve
those lost items.

35:35.758 --> 35:39.011
-Those items were stolen,
Mrs. Hastings.
-You're right.

35:39.011 --> 35:44.600
You're absolutely right.
But my understanding now is,
we dropped those charges.

35:46.394 --> 35:48.437
I'm pressing charges.
That's why Lucy's
being held.

35:48.437 --> 35:50.940
I see.

35:50.940 --> 35:56.529
-And you feel that's best?
-Mrs. Hastings, Lucy is a heroin
addict and a street whore.

35:56.529 --> 36:00.324
Her body and mind are both sick,
and she won't face any of that.

36:00.324 --> 36:02.743
I just can't believe
jail is the solution.

36:02.743 --> 36:05.872
-Are you gonna bail her out?
-I-I can't imagine
it's the solution.

36:05.872 --> 36:09.125
No. No, it's not.
Jail's a terrible place,

36:09.125 --> 36:11.127
but Lucy's in
a terrible place already.

36:11.127 --> 36:13.546
I can't see any other way
to make her understand that.

36:13.546 --> 36:17.842
Well, couldn't she just stay
where she is in the hospital,
with the guard outside?

36:17.842 --> 36:22.597
Mrs. Hastings,
I don't want to
hurt your feelings,

36:22.597 --> 36:25.600
but the way you're thinking
is helping to keep
your daughter sick.

36:25.600 --> 36:28.477
Lucy has to face
the truth without someone...

36:28.477 --> 36:31.147
protecting her, or else
she won't face it at all,

36:31.147 --> 36:33.900
and then she's gonna
wind up dead.

36:33.900 --> 36:37.403
-I know you don't want that.
-My husband is dying,

36:37.403 --> 36:39.989
and now you're saying
my daughter may die?

36:42.825 --> 36:46.996
I'm saying your daughter
has to learn how to live.

36:46.996 --> 36:50.166
-I wasn't anywheres around her.
-'Cause we told you
not to be, right, Jimmy?

36:50.166 --> 36:54.587
-Yeah, you're in big
compliance with the law.
-Sit down. Sit down!

36:56.422 --> 37:00.218
And the next time
you murder somebody,
asshole, change your shoes.

37:00.218 --> 37:02.094
The lab is gonna run
that shoe, Jimmy,

37:02.094 --> 37:05.056
and if that's Angela's
blood, you are going down
for murder, man.

37:05.056 --> 37:06.724
If that's blood, I don't
know how that got there.

37:06.724 --> 37:10.394
Right now, we got
cold-blooded murder.
If it went that way, fine,

37:10.394 --> 37:13.606
don't give no statement up--
we got a lot of pimp murders
go that way.

37:13.606 --> 37:17.026
You know, it didn't go down
like that! I ain't no pimp.

37:17.026 --> 37:20.238
So, what?
Was it the operation?
Huh, Jimmy?

37:20.238 --> 37:23.199
Did that enter into it?
(sighs heavily)

37:24.533 --> 37:27.411
She had me doing things
that was never who I was.

37:27.411 --> 37:29.664
Out there on the stroll,
giving me her money.

37:29.664 --> 37:34.418
I wanted a wife and a home!
She's treating me like a pimp.

37:34.418 --> 37:37.672
So what happened on the street?

37:37.672 --> 37:39.882
It was just like you said.

37:39.882 --> 37:44.887
We was beefin' about
the operation. She says
she's going out to work.

37:44.887 --> 37:48.516
I get all messed up drinking,
and I go out looking for her.

37:50.017 --> 37:52.478
It all extends out of that.

37:52.478 --> 37:56.857
You find her with a john?
Jimmy, that make you upset?

37:56.857 --> 37:59.110
(sniffles)

37:59.110 --> 38:03.698
(shivers)
When I met her,

38:03.698 --> 38:06.742
I thought she was
the most beautiful... girl.

38:08.494 --> 38:10.663
(sobbing)

38:10.663 --> 38:15.710
And I'm not a fag! You can't
just turn yourself into that!

38:19.922 --> 38:22.466
You want to write this up?

38:22.466 --> 38:25.803
Be dancing sometimes.

38:25.803 --> 38:27.805
Slow dancing.

38:30.725 --> 38:34.687
Be holding her.

38:34.687 --> 38:37.273
She was so sweet.

38:39.066 --> 38:41.819
And that smile--
(chuckling)

38:43.487 --> 38:48.701
"That's it, baby.
Don't change nothin'.

38:48.701 --> 38:50.619
Just do how you are."

38:54.290 --> 38:55.750
And you just killed her?

38:55.750 --> 38:59.295
(sobbing)

39:11.766 --> 39:13.559
(door opening)

39:13.559 --> 39:17.396
-Cortez writing his statement?
-Simone's got
the better rapport.

39:17.396 --> 39:21.359
-Okay.
-Could I buy some of
your laundry detergent?

39:22.151 --> 39:25.738
I've decided not
to sell that in the squad.

39:25.738 --> 39:29.283
-Detergent specifically?
-Yeah. The whole product line.

39:29.283 --> 39:33.204
At some point, if people
want to contact Lillian,
that's between them and her.

39:33.204 --> 39:36.332
-How'd you come to that?
-Well, being in
a position of authority,

39:36.332 --> 39:40.419
-it made me uncomfortable.
-This isn't directed at me?

39:40.419 --> 39:44.090
-What are you talking about?
-You're not selling to others,
but not to me?

39:44.090 --> 39:46.759
-No.
-(door opens)

39:48.094 --> 39:51.263
-Hey.
-Hey, Greg,
how you feeling?

39:51.263 --> 39:54.225
(sighs)
Oh, yeah, better.
I'm up to 4:00 to 12:00.

39:54.225 --> 39:58.020
Such an imbecile.
I know Thai food
don't agree with me.

39:58.020 --> 39:59.939
-Hey, Greg.
-Hey.

39:59.939 --> 40:05.277
That guy's writing, boss.
I got the five.
You wanna take off?

40:05.277 --> 40:09.782
So, boss, uh, you think
vitamins help me, uh, fight off
my upset so successfully?

40:09.782 --> 40:13.202
You know that's not logical.
Don't say that 'cause it's
Lillian's franchise.

40:16.789 --> 40:18.624
Well, I'm going home. Night.

40:28.384 --> 40:30.761
Don't move, Medavoy.

40:37.309 --> 40:40.271
♪♪

40:50.614 --> 40:53.409
-WAITER:
Here you go.
-Thanks.

40:53.409 --> 40:54.827
-He saw the ring.
-Oh, yeah?

40:54.827 --> 40:58.789
-Mm-hmm.
-You think he's
gonna call the boss?

40:58.789 --> 41:02.042
(chuckling)
Having to keep everything
secret, Bobby,

41:02.042 --> 41:04.503
that's why a church wedding
doesn't really make sense.

41:04.503 --> 41:07.173
Yeah, there's so many people
that we care about
we can't even invite.

41:07.173 --> 41:11.635
Mm. I understand the job,
not wanting married people
to work together.

41:11.635 --> 41:14.930
I just--I wish they would
make an exception for us.

41:17.475 --> 41:22.438
A city hall wedding
definitely don't strike me
as being too romantic.

41:22.438 --> 41:24.940
Maybe we could drive
to Connecticut somewhere.

41:24.940 --> 41:27.860
Yeah.

41:27.860 --> 41:31.071
SIMONE: Oh, man.
RUSSELL: What?

41:31.071 --> 41:33.073
The waiter, he took too
long bringing your sherbet.

41:34.575 --> 41:38.078
-What's the matter?
-Hey, Robert.

41:38.078 --> 41:43.083
Hey, how's it going there, Joe?
Diane Russell, Joe Salvo.

41:43.083 --> 41:45.461
-Pleasure, Diane.
-Hi.

41:45.461 --> 41:49.340
-Sit down?
-No, I got people.

41:49.340 --> 41:53.594
-So, you still
with the department?
-Yeah, I am. How 'bout you?

41:53.594 --> 41:55.721
-Yeah, I got my application in.
-(chuckles)

41:55.721 --> 41:58.974
What do they pay you, 50?
With overtime?

41:58.974 --> 42:03.479
-Oh, opening up my paychecks.
-Best-looking guy.

42:03.479 --> 42:06.774
Smartest. Had to get cursed
with a conscience, huh, Bobby?

42:06.774 --> 42:09.610
-Anyways, good to see you, Joe.
-I'd like to sit down
with you sometime.

42:09.610 --> 42:14.406
-Yeah, we should work that out.
-Take care, Robert.

42:18.327 --> 42:20.871
-Wiseguy?
-Independent.

42:20.871 --> 42:24.542
Stickup guy.
I guess maybe he pays
the wiseguys some tribute.

42:24.542 --> 42:28.504
(chuckles) Someday,
I know, I'm gonna meet all
the upstanding citizens...

42:28.504 --> 42:32.049
-from your neighborhood.
-I don't how
I got through the net.

42:32.049 --> 42:38.264
-You want to get outta here?
-No, I want to talk to
my girl about our wedding.

42:38.264 --> 42:40.307
-I like the Connecticut idea.
-Yeah?

42:40.307 --> 42:42.226
-Yeah.
-From Mr. Salvo.

42:42.226 --> 42:44.937
Tell Mr. Salvo,
"Thank you very much."
We're pretty well done here.

42:44.937 --> 42:50.526
-This is a dessert wine.
-Hey, I know what that is.
Tell him we don't want it.

42:50.526 --> 42:53.946
(softly)
We're going.

42:53.946 --> 42:56.240
-Hmm.
-I guess Joe...

42:56.240 --> 42:59.577
is not gonna let us
work out getting married.

42:59.577 --> 43:03.205
Joe don't let us
work out getting married,
I'll shoot him in the head.

43:03.205 --> 43:08.377
You just make sure you
get the drop on him, 'cause
he will shoot you first.

43:08.377 --> 43:10.379
Ready?
Come on.

43:18.012 --> 43:21.015
♪♪
